Alanson C. Noble, complainant, et al., defendants in error, v. Quin O’Brien, plaintiff in error.Gen. No. 26,681.Suit for an accounting between attorneys as to fees. Decree for complainant. Error to the Cir.euit Court of Cook county; the Hon. Charles M. Walker and Hon. George Ered Bush,. Judges, presiding. Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the March term, 1921.Beversed and remanded with directions.

Barnes, J., dissenting in part.

Opinion filed March 21, 1922.Certiorari denied by Supreme . Court (making opinion final).Quin O’Brien, pro se and James C. Byrne, for plaintiff in error; John P. McGoorty and Martin J. Isaaes, of counsel. Timothy D. Hurley, for defendant in error Alanson C. Noble. Charles L. Bartlett and Herbert W. Becker, for defendant in error Chicago Title & Trust Company. Mr. Presiding Justice Gridley

delivered the opinion of the court.
